Calculated decay rates for tangential dipole orientation for a 2a = 50 nm Ag solid sphere versus emission wavelength λ and spacing Δr. (a) Radiative decay rate; (b) Total decay rate; (c,d) show the same as (a,b) but for an extra h = 10 nm dielectric shell with ns = 1.4. Ambient refractive index n = 1. Note linear scale everywhere. White areas correspond to decay rate enhancement. For the core-shell case the Δr is a distance from a dipole to the outer shell surface, i.e., Δr = r0 − (h + a).

